----+++ Literature

	* Overview of visualization techniques
	* What aspects to visualize
	* What tools are already available

----+++ Case Study: Understanding the Linux Kernel

	* Develop a set of tools for visualizing aspects of C programs using Stratego and the XT tool set

	* Discover which parts are
		* generic 
		* specific for the language model
		* specific to the language (C)

	* Try to separate these parts such that the generic elements can be reused for other languages

----+++ Visualizations

	* Call-graph
		* how to visualize higher-order functions / function pointers / methods
	* Module / package structure
		* Discover modules / remodularize
		* Clustering

